Column Comment.0: LAND SALE BID SET IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for a land sale bidding set.
Column Comment.1: ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating whether this row of data is currently eitheractive / valid (Y) or inactive / invalid (N).
Column Comment.2: R LAND BID STATUS: The current status of the bid, such as pending, successful,unsucessful etc.
Column Comment.3: CONFIDENTIAL_IND: Indicates that a bid set is confidential. In this case, bidding isoften handled through a broker.
Column Comment.4: CONTINGENCY DESCRIPTION: A textual description of the type of contingencyplaced on processing the bids.
Column Comment.5: CONTINGENCY INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating that dependencies exist betweenbids. If set to yes, the bids are usually placed contingent to the success or failure ofother bids in the set.
Column Comment.6: EFFECTIVE DATE: The date that the data in this row first came into effect.
Column Comment.7: EXPIRY DATE: The date that the data in this row was no longer active or in effect.
Column Comment.8: OWNER BUSINESS ASSOCIATE ID: The identifier for the business associate who isthe owner or manager of the bid set.
Column Comment.9: ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global uniqueidentifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used,optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the datamodel DDL should be created.
Column Comment.10: REMARK: Narrative remarks about this row of data.
Column Comment.11: BID STATUS DATE: the date that the status indicated in the BID STATUS columnwas effective.
Column Comment.12: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.13: SUCCESSFUL INDICATOR: A Y/N flag that indicates whether the bid set wassuccessful or not. The success of individual bids may be tracked at the bid level inLAND SALE BID.
Column Comment.14: ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.
Column Comment.15: ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.
Column Comment.16: ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.
Column Comment.17: ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.
Column Comment.18: ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of datais effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data wasmade available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.19: ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data isno longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row ofdata was no longer available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.20: PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row,usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, althoughother types of quality reference are permitted.
